==English==

===Etymology===
Via Spanish or portuguese ''casta'' for "[[Lineage]]", "[[breed]]" or "[[race]]", from Latin ''casta'', the feminine form of ''casto'', "pure". 

===Pronunciation===
*käst, /kɑːst/, /<tt>kA:st</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[cast]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɑːst|Rhymes: -ɑːst]]

===Noun===
'''caste''' ([[castes]])

#Indian [[hereditary]] social [[class]]

